#, no-wrap
msgid "Charter for the Cluster Administrators"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Lead cluster administrator is a delegated officer role (aka. \"hat\") that "
"answers to the FreeBSD Core Team and ultimately the FreeBSD community at "
"large. This person shall have the operational authority over the FreeBSD "
"cluster infrastructure (to the extent that the Core Team can delegate this "
"authority) and will be responsible for the following in general:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Ensure the reliable operation of the Project's equipment and network "
"resources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:12
msgid ""
"Ensure that the Project's resources are suitably and effectively used to "
"serve the Project's interests."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Ensure that reasonable security precautions and mitigations are implemented "
"within the constraints of the nature of a highly distributed project."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Delegate to and coordinating with both the site-specific admin teams and the "
"admins at large."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Ensure that standard operating procedures, rules, guidelines etc are "
"documented and understandable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:16
msgid ""
"Take measures to ensure that a competent administrator would be expected to "
"be able to adopt a predecessor's work in a reasonable amount of time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Contingency planning and implementation to ensure continuity across site "
"specific problems (including donated site withdrawal or outages)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Keep the interested parties (Core Team, Security Team, FreeBSD Foundation, "
"Ports Management Team, etc), project members and community members "
"appropriately informed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Give timely and authoritive answers to questions, or a direct referral to "
"the appropriate party."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:20
msgid "Aid other hat wearers and cluster administrators to get their job done."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:21
msgid ""
"Where practical and appropriate, use the Project's own product as a proving "
"ground."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:22
msgid ""
"Make sure that it is easy for developers to know what hardware resources "
"they have access to for project purposes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:24
msgid ""
"The lead cluster administrator answers to the FreeBSD Core Team. If a party "
"is unhappy with a position that the hat wearer takes and is unable to change "
"their mind, they may take the issue to the Core Team. The Core Team has the "
"final say in the matter. If the lead cluster administrator is a member of "
"the Core Team then a complaint may be made in confidence via the core "
"secretary or another member if desired."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:26
msgid "Any of the following still require a sign-off from the Core Team:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:28
msgid "New public facing services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:29
msgid "Planned withdrawal of public facing services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:30
msgid "New team members."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:32
msgid "Notable interaction with other hats:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:34
msgid ""
"The lead cluster administrator will consult with the Security Officer and "
"the Security Team where appropriate but will be responsible for making "
"decisions. However, the Security Officer may respond to security emergencies "
"involving project infrastructure as necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:35
msgid ""
"The Ports Management Team has a large resource footprint and arrangements "
"will be made with them to effectively operate their resources within the "
"constraints of the overall cluster operation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:37
msgid "Earmarked resources:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/clusteradm.adoc:38
msgid ""
"Some site resources are provided for specific purposes. Any such earmarking "
"or use restrictions will be documented to make sure such resources are used "
"as intended."
msgstr ""
